Class Wordlist

All Implemented Interfaces:
SoftWoehr, verbose
public class Wordlist
extends Semantic
implements SoftWoehr, verbose

This is a word list of Semantics. They are keyed by their names. If a Semantic of an existing name is keyed in, the previous is lost.

Version:
$Revision: 1.1.1.1 $
Author:
$Author: jwoehr $

put

public void put(Semantic s)
Add a Semantic in, comes with its own key. If key already exists, push the previous Semantic for the key (so that it can later be restored if the user 'forget's the active Semantic) and set the active Semantic to the Semantic presented to this method.

defaultWordlist

public static Wordlist defaultWordlist()
Create a default wordlist for initial engine. Each invocation of this method results in a unique instance. Alternatively, the list could be a static member, but then it had better be read-only to interpreter instances due to its being shared.
